{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, the price of anarchy measures how the joint welfare of a system degrades due to selfishness by dividing the welfare value for the \"worst-case\" decentralized equilibrium with the welfare at its optimal centralized configuration (Koutsoupias and Papadimitriou 2009).",
    "80 But these tools might be of less use from the perspective of individual agents.",
    "We can imagine that an agent has managed to compute a \"golden rule\" strategy profile (e.g., a set of action-rules) 79 See also chapter 7 in Cesa-Bianchi and Lugosi (2006).",
    "80 Conversely, the price of stability gives a ratio of the difference between \"best possible\" decentralized equilibrium and the optimal centralized solution.",
    "which for any possible interaction, maximizes the joint benefit of her society."
  ]
}